description: The annual Rites of Passage Ceremony is a pre-commencement celebration that centers the experiences and culture of Black and Latine-identified students who, through resolute persistence, have completed an undergraduate or graduate degree at Rutgers University–New Brunswick. The event recognizes their accomplishments, hard work, and dedication while acknowledging the substantial efforts of our student’s families and networks of support. Distinguished speakers, student awards, performances, and the incorporation of African and Latine culture and traditions—specifically the culminating Kente Stole presentation—all add to the vibrancy of this celebratory day. Participation in the Rites of Passage Ceremony is open to all Rutgers University—New Brunswick Undergraduate and Graduate students who have earned their degrees between January 2025 and August 2025.  Rites of Passage 2025 Registration is officially Closed! We look forward to seeing all of our graduates at JMA!  To participate, students must have registered by Friday, May 2nd, 2025 through the getINVOLVED portal. Only students registered by the deadline will be guaranteed Rites of Passage graduate perks and able to ensure you have tickets for guests.   All graduates are required to wear their academic regalia, which can be purchased from the Barnes and Noble Rutgers University Bookstore on Somerset Street. There is no cost to participate in Rites of Passage for graduates or guests. All graduates who register will receive the following:-1 Free Kente Cloth Stole-7 guest tickets-Access to reception - Digital Invitation Downloads  If you have specific questions about your registration or the ceremony, please email rop@echo.rutgers.edu. Please note that all graduates need to be checked-in between 2:30-3:30pm. The graduation will start promptly at 4:00pm.  Visit the Rites of Passage website for more information!
name: 33rd Annual Rites of Passage Ceremony Registration
organizationNames: Center for Latino Arts and Culture

description: We were all heartbroken about the cancellation of GRIB, so I wanted to at least plan one small seminar with a very cool invited speaker! Dr. Joshua Anthony (husband to our own Dr. Tracy Anthony) is the founder and CEO of Nlumn, a company specializing in business-to-business personalized health/nutrition consultations. He will be presenting on a span of topics, ranging from the research underpinning personalized nutrition, to working with the public, to navigating federal and state regulations. We'll have a change to mingle with him before his seminar and enjoy Efes, then attend the seminar after. I'm looking forward to seeing you all there!
name: Dr. Joshua Anthony Seminar on Personalized Nutrition
